{"word":"φώς","slug":"φώς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φώς</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>used by Poets, just like <a href='S:ἀνήρ'><el>ἀνήρ</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a man</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a man</i>, as <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> a woman, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>δύ' οἰκτρὼ φῶτε</el>, of a man and his wife, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>a man</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> a god, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}